miracle /ˈmɪrəkəl/

(miracles) 

1. N-COUNT If you say that a good event is a miracle , you mean that it is very surprising and unexpected. 奇迹 

例： It is a miracle no one was killed. 没有人死亡真是个奇迹。 

2. ADJ A miracle drug or product does something that was thought almost impossible. 神奇的 [journalism] [ADJ n] 

例： ...the miracle drugs that keep his 94-year-old mother healthy. …使他那94岁高龄的老母亲保持健康的神奇药物。 

3. N-COUNT A miracle is a wonderful and surprising event that is believed to be caused by God. 上帝创造的奇迹 

例： ...Jesus's ability to perform miracles. …耶稣行神的能力。

</div>

